comments: Walker IV (SAS) steps out of bounds.
Tatum (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position on DeRozan (SAS) during the drive.
Murray (SAS) makes marginal contact with Tatum (BOS).
Poeltl (SAS) jumps to the side of Brown (BOS) to contest the shot attempt. Brown slips the contact and uses his off-arm to create incidental contact with Poeltl's shoulder.
Mills (SAS) sets the screen on Smart (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Thompson (BOS) extends his leg towards DeRozan (SAS) and initiates contact that affects his shot attempt.
Johnson (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position on Brown (BOS) during the drive.
Poeltl (SAS) makes marginal contact with Theis's (BOS) arm during his dunk.
Brown (BOS) makes marginal contact with DeRozan (SAS) as he receives the pass.
Aldridge (SAS) sets the screen on Brown (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Thompson (BOS) legally contests DeRozan (SAS) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Mills (SAS) and Tatum (BOS) engage and disengage after the screen.
Murray (SAS) makes contact with the ball to dislodge it from Walker (BOS). Any contact after the ball is loose is incidental.
Theis (BOS) sets the screen on Murray (SAS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Poeltl (SAS) makes marginal contact with Tatum's (BOS) arm and does not affect his shot attempt.
Smart (BOS) makes marginal contact with DeRozan (SAS) as he gathers the ball.
Brown (BOS) commits a take foul on Gay (SAS).
Murray (SAS) makes marginal contact with Walker (BOS) at the end of the drive.
Theis (BOS) commits a take foul on Gay (SAS).
